WEBVTT

00:21.847 --> 00:24.241
[thunder clapping]

00:26.200 --> 00:28.289
[heavy breathing]

00:28.811 --> 00:29.855
-[inaudible voice over radio]
-[man shouting]

00:30.030 --> 00:31.422
[heavy breathing]

00:32.075 --> 00:33.511
[machine gun fire]

00:35.035 --> 00:36.645
[machine gun fire]

00:37.907 --> 00:39.561
[machine gun fire]

00:40.083 --> 00:44.957
-[heavy breathing]
-[men shouting]

02:18.573 --> 02:23.273
[loud beep]

02:26.102 --> 02:28.626
[dog barking in distance]

02:30.976 --> 02:32.978
[ambient music]

02:33.065 --> 02:36.678
[man grunts]

02:37.766 --> 02:42.814
[ambient music continues]

02:59.309 --> 03:01.355
[baby coos]

03:04.184 --> 03:05.402
[baby cries in distance]

03:06.621 --> 03:07.665
[man sighs]

03:11.321 --> 03:13.236
[baby coos]

03:15.717 --> 03:17.153
Good mornin'.

03:20.069 --> 03:21.810
What you got? Let me see this.

03:22.593 --> 03:24.247
-Oh. Whoosh.
-[baby coos]

03:25.640 --> 03:28.382
Yeah. What's that? Boop boop.

03:29.034 --> 03:31.385
[toy jingles]

03:33.865 --> 03:35.650
What do you think?

03:36.346 --> 03:38.130
Wah!

03:39.043 --> 03:42.744
[suspenseful music plays]

03:48.576 --> 03:50.534
What's that necklace for?

03:51.753 --> 03:56.018
[music continues]

03:57.192 --> 03:59.326
[babbles]

04:01.806 --> 04:03.939
[laughing]

04:04.461 --> 04:05.854
[baby coos]

04:06.333 --> 04:08.813
[ambient music continues]

04:09.771 --> 04:11.163
[door swings open]

04:11.251 --> 04:13.383
-Hello!
-Good morning, Meme.

04:13.470 --> 04:14.950
Morning, Jamie.

04:17.430 --> 04:19.041
-[kisses]
-Ah!

04:19.128 --> 04:21.913
You hand over that baby to me
right this minute.

04:22.000 --> 04:23.828
-Who's that?
-Who's my heart?

04:23.915 --> 04:25.265
Who's that?

04:25.352 --> 04:26.744
-Aww.
-Oh.

04:26.918 --> 04:29.573
-That's it, come to Meme.
-[baby coos happily]

04:36.580 --> 04:38.756
Thank you for doing this, Meme.

04:41.977 --> 04:44.371
-[baby cries]
-Aww aww.

04:44.457 --> 04:47.417
-That's a grumpy baby.
-[baby cries]

04:47.504 --> 04:50.202
Oh! One more goodbye, yeah?

04:50.290 --> 04:52.770
You gonna stay
with Meme today, yeah?

04:52.857 --> 04:54.511
Yeah.

04:54.598 --> 04:56.687
Be good. Be a good girl.

04:58.689 --> 05:00.343
You all right
staying the night?

05:00.430 --> 05:03.259
[Meme]
Aww... oh! 'Course, darlin'.

05:03.346 --> 05:06.262
-Nothing would make me happier.
-[baby cries]

05:06.349 --> 05:08.177
-Oh, my!
-[baby cries]

05:08.264 --> 05:11.180
-Papas leavin'.
-I'll be back today.

05:11.267 --> 05:13.661
[Meme] Daddy will be back.
He'll be back.

05:13.748 --> 05:15.532
-Thank you, Meme.
-He'll be back.

05:17.665 --> 05:20.972
-[door shuts]
-[intro music plays]

05:36.161 --> 05:41.819
[intro music continues]

06:05.843 --> 06:07.932
[van brakes]

06:11.545 --> 06:12.894
[van door closes]

06:18.769 --> 06:24.471
[intro music plays]

06:27.038 --> 06:28.562
[gun cocks]

06:58.766 --> 07:01.333
All right, so there I was.

07:01.421 --> 07:03.771
Day two, in the sandbox.

07:04.336 --> 07:06.687
In a convoy, on the 81st.

07:06.774 --> 07:08.689
I'm sittin' up top,
at the gunner seat.

07:08.776 --> 07:11.256
Fucking hearts beating
through my chest 'cause I...

07:11.343 --> 07:13.737
I heard it's the most dangerous
stretch of road in the country.

07:13.824 --> 07:15.260
Fuck yeah, it is.

07:15.347 --> 07:17.001
What could go wrong?

07:17.088 --> 07:19.177
So we're cruising along.

07:19.264 --> 07:22.093
All of a sudden,
I see this fucking Hajji
on the side of the road.

07:22.180 --> 07:24.052
And he's going to town

07:24.139 --> 07:26.141
-on a fuckin donkey--
-He's got--

07:26.228 --> 07:28.970
Hang on a minute!
A fucking donkey?

07:29.057 --> 07:30.928
Bro, he's got
his little Hajji dress

07:31.015 --> 07:33.844
hiked up over his shoulders
bangin' away.

07:33.931 --> 07:36.891
-How do you even do that?
-Super fucking weird, right?

07:39.546 --> 07:42.636
I even said somethin' to Gunny
about it but he shrugs it off.

07:43.506 --> 07:45.769
So we don't get another
six klicks down the road,

07:45.856 --> 07:49.164
I see another fucking Alibaba
off in the distance

07:49.251 --> 07:52.384
ridin' one of his own
behind this broken down Humvee.

07:52.472 --> 07:55.431
What, like another donkey
in the butthole?

07:55.518 --> 07:57.912
-[laughs]
-So what happened next?

07:57.999 --> 07:59.435
More of the same.
I must've seen like

07:59.522 --> 08:01.002
fuckin' four more pairs of 'em.

08:01.089 --> 08:04.092
Gettin' after it on the way back
to the farm. right?

08:04.179 --> 08:05.789
What?

08:05.876 --> 08:08.270
-So... uh...
-[rubs hands together]

08:08.357 --> 08:10.315
It gets worse.
All right, so we get back

08:10.402 --> 08:13.449
to the motor pool
and I see this old dirty bastard

08:13.536 --> 08:15.538
about yay high,
with a wooden leg

08:15.625 --> 08:20.021
sittin' on the hood
of the major's Humvee,
jerkin' off.

08:20.108 --> 08:21.457
-You're kidding.
-What?

08:21.936 --> 08:24.025
-Yeah--
-How the fuck do you
even get in there?

08:24.112 --> 08:27.550
So Gunny looks up to me,
can see how fuckin' rattled
I am, right?

08:27.637 --> 08:30.901
Then he asks me what
my malfunction is.
I mean, my malfunction,

08:30.988 --> 08:32.599
I'm telling you, the whole
fucking way here I'm seeing

08:32.686 --> 08:35.297
dudes bangin' donkeys
on the side of the road.

08:35.384 --> 08:37.168
There's this guy
with a wooden leg

08:37.255 --> 08:39.475
beatin' off in the motor pool
in broad daylight

08:39.562 --> 08:40.823
and you know what he says to me?

08:41.172 --> 08:42.522
What'd he say?

08:44.611 --> 08:48.223
"Marine, you can't expect a guy
with a wooden leg

08:48.310 --> 08:49.833
to catch a fucking donkey."

08:50.442 --> 08:52.227
-[men laughing]
-Crazy motherfucker.

08:52.314 --> 08:54.055
-[laughing continues]
-Jesus Christ.

08:54.142 --> 08:55.360
We here.

08:58.276 --> 09:00.104
What's your problem?
Why you poutin'?

09:00.191 --> 09:01.802
Bitch, I ain't fuckin' poutin'.

09:03.281 --> 09:05.327
-Yeah, you are.
-Fuck you.

09:07.285 --> 09:08.591
Let's rock and roll.

09:11.463 --> 09:15.859
[suspenseful music]

09:19.428 --> 09:21.517
I know the transfer took
a little bit longer
than we wanted,

09:21.604 --> 09:23.345
but we appreciate your business

09:23.432 --> 09:25.390
[man groans]
andwe appreciate your trust.

09:25.477 --> 09:28.437
Everybody freeze!
Don't you fuckin' move!

09:28.524 --> 09:30.526
-[woman screams, moans]
-Hands away from
the weapons, all.

09:30.613 --> 09:32.006
-Nah nah nah nah nah.
-Think it through.

09:32.093 --> 09:33.573
-[woman panicking]
-Everybody fuckin' relax.

09:33.660 --> 09:35.444
You heard him.
Don't fuckin' move.

09:37.098 --> 09:38.795
-Stop!
-Shut up!

09:41.537 --> 09:44.322
All right, you heard the man.

09:44.409 --> 09:46.498
Let's start with
you three ladies right there.

09:46.586 --> 09:49.240
Hands laced on top of your head.
Back away from the counter.

09:50.633 --> 09:53.462
Let's go.
Get against the fucking wall.
Everyone else, on the floor!

09:53.549 --> 09:55.986
Eyes on the fucking floor, pal.

09:56.552 --> 09:58.728
-Get on the floor, bitch!
-[woman groans and hits ground]

09:58.815 --> 10:01.557
-Whoa!
-Guys, just relax! All right?

10:01.644 --> 10:05.343
Heads down. Eyes down.
This ain't worth dying for.

10:05.430 --> 10:07.084
[suspenseful music plays]

10:07.171 --> 10:09.347
Give me the fucking key.

10:09.434 --> 10:12.089
[suspenseful music plays]

10:12.176 --> 10:13.613
-Give me the fucking key!
-[key clangs]

10:13.700 --> 10:15.136
Smart!

10:19.053 --> 10:20.663
-[man groans painfully]
-[woman screams]

10:24.928 --> 10:26.582
[man groans]

10:28.758 --> 10:30.760
-[woman] No no no no no!
-[bones break]

10:30.847 --> 10:32.544
-Ah ah!
-Oh, God! Oh, my--!

10:32.806 --> 10:35.722
-Ah!
-Shut the fuck up,
or your fucking thumb's next.

10:35.809 --> 10:37.724
-[keys rattle]
-[woman crying]

10:40.509 --> 10:42.119
Let's go. I need the code.

10:42.206 --> 10:44.861
Ah! Three, 17, 77.

10:49.083 --> 10:54.436
[suspenseful music plays]

10:58.266 --> 11:01.748
Look at my fucking eyes,
if that's a panic code...

11:01.835 --> 11:05.447
he's gonna cut off a lot more
than your fucking thumb.

11:05.534 --> 11:07.231
You understand me?

11:08.276 --> 11:09.451
[shudders]

11:09.538 --> 11:13.281
One, 23, seven, nine.

11:13.716 --> 11:16.458
-You, motha--
-[woman screams]

11:16.632 --> 11:19.461
-Shut the fuck up!
-[keypad pings]

11:19.853 --> 11:22.203
-[door beeps]
-We're in!

11:22.290 --> 11:25.554
-[woman] Uh-uh-uh.
-Whoa!

11:32.213 --> 11:34.215
[inaudible radio chatter]

11:42.005 --> 11:46.575
[suspenseful music]

11:49.883 --> 11:51.711
Bro, we're out of clock.

12:28.965 --> 12:30.750
Clear!

12:31.446 --> 12:32.752
Clear!

12:42.370 --> 12:43.763
[glass shatters]

12:45.808 --> 12:47.027
Now!

12:47.114 --> 12:48.506
-[gunshot]
-Ah!

12:49.290 --> 12:52.206
-Cops at rear!
-[heavy gun fire]

12:52.293 --> 12:55.383
-Move back!
-Wait!

12:55.470 --> 12:57.907
-All clear! All clear!
-[heavy gunfire]

13:00.649 --> 13:02.694
[suspenseful music]

13:02.782 --> 13:04.087
Wait for it! Wait for it!

13:06.829 --> 13:09.266
-Contacts left!
-[heavy gunfire]

13:10.746 --> 13:11.921
-[men shouting]
-[excessive gunfire]

13:12.008 --> 13:13.705
-Move!
-[heavy gunfire]

13:15.620 --> 13:21.409
[heavy gunfire continues]

13:31.332 --> 13:33.160
-[inaudible shouting]
-Move!

13:48.218 --> 13:49.829
Let it go! Hey!

13:50.873 --> 13:52.701
We said to... only.

14:19.249 --> 14:20.729
Motherfuck!

14:30.957 --> 14:33.611
Move back! Move--

14:33.698 --> 14:34.961
Moving.

14:40.967 --> 14:42.490
-Move!
-Move it!

14:49.062 --> 14:55.024
[police sirens approaching]

14:59.986 --> 15:01.422
Contact right!

15:23.705 --> 15:27.883
-Hey! Spread out, to your left!
-Move!

15:29.711 --> 15:31.104
Moving!

15:33.149 --> 15:34.542
That's it.

15:49.600 --> 15:50.993
Reloading!

15:52.299 --> 15:53.430
Move!

15:54.866 --> 15:56.868
-Oh!
-Moving!

16:01.438 --> 16:02.744
Back there!

16:08.706 --> 16:10.186
Move!

16:12.101 --> 16:13.624
Moving!

16:14.582 --> 16:17.498
We're clear!
Code, move!

16:18.194 --> 16:19.282
Moving!

16:23.112 --> 16:24.461
[inaudible yelling]

16:32.774 --> 16:33.993
Reloading!

16:39.955 --> 16:41.870
-Move!
-Moving!

16:43.263 --> 16:44.612
We're clear!

16:48.268 --> 16:52.446
Hey! Wait out on me,
wait out on me! Move!

16:52.533 --> 16:54.926
-Moving!
-Wait up!

16:56.841 --> 16:57.929
Move!

17:07.635 --> 17:09.593
Move! Move!

17:36.229 --> 17:38.492
-Fuck! Shit!
-Come on!

17:38.579 --> 17:41.190
-Ah!
-Hey!

17:41.277 --> 17:42.844
What the fuck
are you doing, man?

17:45.412 --> 17:46.587
Let's go.

17:46.674 --> 17:48.110
Come on! Let's go.

17:48.197 --> 17:49.633
Keep your fuckin' head down,
all right?

17:49.720 --> 17:51.418
All right, come on.
Go walk!

17:58.903 --> 18:01.297
Get some! Get some! Get some!

18:03.343 --> 18:06.824
[rap music plays on radio]

18:11.525 --> 18:13.048
Out of the car!

18:13.744 --> 18:15.050
Put your head down!

18:15.137 --> 18:17.139
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

18:21.535 --> 18:23.102
[brakes squeal]

18:23.189 --> 18:24.973
[grunts]

18:25.060 --> 18:26.757
Get the fuck in, Vic!

18:26.844 --> 18:28.716
-Let's fuckin' go!
-Drive!

18:29.369 --> 18:31.153
[tires squeal]

18:32.198 --> 18:33.938
[grunting]

18:34.243 --> 18:36.419
-Left, left!
-[tires squeal]

18:47.256 --> 18:48.475
Fuck!

18:49.650 --> 18:50.955
Back, back, back!

18:54.263 --> 18:55.786
[heavy gunfire]

19:00.965 --> 19:02.576
[tires squeal]

19:09.017 --> 19:10.801
Come on, motherfuckers.

19:10.888 --> 19:12.151
Come on...

19:15.371 --> 19:16.764
[grunts]

19:17.460 --> 19:19.201
Turn here! Here!

19:19.288 --> 19:21.812
[tires squeal]

19:29.994 --> 19:31.822
[groans]

19:33.476 --> 19:34.608
-Come on, come on!
-[heavy breathing]

19:36.566 --> 19:39.656
-[sirens approaching]
-[man grunts]

19:41.441 --> 19:42.572
[car engine starts]

19:48.752 --> 19:50.841
[suspenseful music plays]

19:51.233 --> 19:53.192
[tires squeal]

20:03.767 --> 20:05.943
[grunts]

20:08.772 --> 20:12.123
-Yo, get down!
Get the fuck down!
-[sirens blare]

20:19.914 --> 20:22.960
[dispatch] Dispatch,
we have multiple officers down
at first National Bank,

20:23.047 --> 20:24.484
South Conti and Calhoun.

20:24.571 --> 20:26.355
Requesting air meds for
location, ASAP.

20:26.442 --> 20:28.966
[dispatch 2]
Citywide, all units respond.

20:29.053 --> 20:31.447
-[sirens]
-[dispatch] One, O, eight.
Multiple officers down.

20:31.534 --> 20:33.319
EMS, Code three.

20:33.406 --> 20:36.191
[female dispatch] All units,
suspect vehicle is a 90s model,

20:36.278 --> 20:39.325
light blue, wood paneled,
Chevy station wagon.

20:39.412 --> 20:40.717
Be advised,
suspects are armed.

20:40.804 --> 20:42.763
with fully automatic weapons.

20:43.285 --> 20:45.244
[dispatch]
Notified J.P., Saint Bernard,

20:45.331 --> 20:47.115
Saint Tammany,
and State Police.

20:47.202 --> 20:49.944
Requesting shutdown
of all routes out of the city.

20:50.031 --> 20:52.381
including the Crescent City
Connection,

20:52.468 --> 20:55.645
Causeway, the Twin Span,
and all routes headed
westbound.

20:55.732 --> 20:57.691
[sirens blare]

21:08.963 --> 21:10.965
-Gonna say nothing?
-What you want me to say?

21:11.052 --> 21:12.662
What the fuck was that?

21:13.228 --> 21:15.143
FBI robbery task force.

21:15.230 --> 21:16.362
No shit.

21:17.841 --> 21:20.279
-How'd they know?
-Someone ratted us.

21:21.932 --> 21:23.325
Who?

21:24.848 --> 21:27.590
We gotta wash this money.
Make sure our exit's
not burning,

21:27.677 --> 21:29.331
and get the fuck out.
Fast.

21:29.418 --> 21:31.246
Where we gonna run?

21:32.291 --> 21:34.162
This is gonna
make national news, Mick.

21:34.249 --> 21:35.685
We're fucking cop killers now.

21:35.772 --> 21:37.731
The choice is what?
You hear anybody yell,

21:37.818 --> 21:39.559
"Don't move, you're under
arrest"? No, you didn't.

21:40.995 --> 21:42.562
They were there
to fucking murder us,

21:42.649 --> 21:44.259
and I ain't got no regrets.

21:45.913 --> 21:48.089
We left, fucking,
three of our brothers

21:48.176 --> 21:49.743
in the fucking street!

21:51.571 --> 21:52.789
[beep]

21:53.964 --> 21:55.531
They made their choices.

21:56.227 --> 22:00.536
[suspenseful music]

22:02.190 --> 22:03.844
[engine starts]

22:21.775 --> 22:26.954
[suspenseful music]

22:27.041 --> 22:29.522
Two, I've already given
my statement to your paid men.

22:29.609 --> 22:31.437
-Gentlemen!
-You're probably not--

22:31.741 --> 22:33.090
Pace.

22:36.093 --> 22:37.530
So you're the one in charge
of this shit show.

22:37.617 --> 22:39.227
That's Special Agent
Frank Ross.

22:39.314 --> 22:41.403
Where the fuck were you,
Special Agent?

22:41.490 --> 22:43.927
I just got off a plane from
D.C. ten minutes ago.

22:44.014 --> 22:46.408
I've got six dead officers
and another one in critical

22:46.495 --> 22:48.715
because of your team's
cowboy shit.

22:50.020 --> 22:52.719
I understand, Lieutenant.
I do.

22:52.806 --> 22:54.329
It went bad
and we're here.

22:54.416 --> 22:55.852
We've gotta move past that now,

22:55.939 --> 22:57.985
so we can focus
on catching these guys.

22:58.333 --> 23:01.771
"Catch 'em."
It's New Orleans, Special Agent.

23:01.858 --> 23:04.208
We're gonna bury
these motherfuckers.

23:05.166 --> 23:08.517
Do your thing,
but don't go fucking shit
on my crime scene.

23:09.170 --> 23:11.651
Remember,
this is homicide first,
robbery second.

23:11.738 --> 23:15.481
I understand you're upset.
Emotional.

23:17.308 --> 23:19.006
You have every reason to be...

23:20.137 --> 23:23.314
But if you ever sling
foul language at me again,

23:23.402 --> 23:25.360
it will be your last.

23:26.448 --> 23:27.754
Understand?

23:29.408 --> 23:32.280
[suspenseful music]

23:34.413 --> 23:37.024
So, where we at on lockdown?

23:37.111 --> 23:39.983
In motion, boss.
Mayor's given us the keys.

23:40.070 --> 23:41.768
There are checkpoints
everywhere.

23:41.855 --> 23:43.596
[indistinct], the causeway,
all the ports,

23:43.683 --> 23:45.249
highways, bridges, roads

23:45.336 --> 23:46.816
-heading out the city.
-Marinas?

23:46.903 --> 23:48.209
Yes, sir. Everything.

23:48.296 --> 23:49.993
All right, all right.

23:50.690 --> 23:53.823
I want C.R.T. teams
and every precinct standing by.

23:55.042 --> 23:58.567
-So, what exactly happened?
-I got a call from my buddy
in Vice.

23:58.654 --> 24:01.396
Said he hooked a guy yesterday,
on some sort of statutory shit.

24:01.483 --> 24:03.703
Some nobody, Edwin Smalls.

24:03.790 --> 24:06.967
That cyber security geek is
looking at five to seven years
in Angola.

24:07.054 --> 24:08.534
Folded like a lawn-chair.

24:08.969 --> 24:10.492
They literally called us
ten minutes

24:10.579 --> 24:12.146
before the crew hit the place.

24:12.233 --> 24:13.539
I tried to phone you,
but I couldn't reach you.

24:13.626 --> 24:15.279
So... I made the call.

24:16.455 --> 24:18.935
So, tell me why we couldn't
take 'em at the van.

24:19.719 --> 24:21.590
Well, the block car
was in motion,

24:21.677 --> 24:23.070
and we were pushin' up.

24:23.462 --> 24:25.725
Crew came out heavy
like before, five and a driver.

24:25.855 --> 24:29.032
Body armor, ballistics, masks,
all automatic stuff...

24:29.119 --> 24:30.860
And then, fender bender

24:30.947 --> 24:32.688
right in front of us,
as we were moving in.

24:32.775 --> 24:35.082
Boris Karloff over there,
at the front door,

24:35.169 --> 24:36.910
came up on his sights.

24:37.650 --> 24:40.087
I beat him to the punch.
It was on.

24:40.609 --> 24:42.872
Nico took out the driver
of the van.

24:42.959 --> 24:45.745
Swat got the mummy over there
at the dumpster.

24:45.962 --> 24:48.922
So, I hear you winged a fourth.
You sure you hit him?

24:49.009 --> 24:51.402
Oh, I hit meat.
I heard the man howl.

24:51.490 --> 24:53.274
And, I tell ya,
there ain't no way he makes it

24:53.361 --> 24:55.929
through the night without
some serious medical attention.

24:56.016 --> 24:58.497
These guys are smart,
they're way too ruthless.

24:58.584 --> 25:02.239
Find out if there are any
doctors who've come up missing.

25:02.326 --> 25:06.069
Look into... vet offices,
plastic surgeons,

25:06.156 --> 25:07.549
anyone who can handle trauma.

25:07.636 --> 25:09.203
On it.

25:10.421 --> 25:12.467
You know how you've been saying
you thought these guys
were ex-military.

25:12.554 --> 25:14.730
-Yeah
-Yeah, well, you're right.

25:15.296 --> 25:16.819
We had them pinned down.

25:16.906 --> 25:18.734
and guess what those assholes
go and do?

25:18.821 --> 25:20.997
-Attack the ambush.
-Exactly.

25:21.084 --> 25:23.260
Wasn't till they realized
they were boxed in

25:23.347 --> 25:25.045
that they started to fall back.

25:25.393 --> 25:27.134
And the ranger peeled
all the way down the fence
and out.

25:27.221 --> 25:29.832
-Ranger peel?
-Yeah.

25:29.919 --> 25:33.227
Move, moving, covering,
all at high speed shit.

25:35.055 --> 25:37.753
I gotta tell you,
I haven't seen that live
since Somalia.

25:38.841 --> 25:43.454
-Go on.
-They jacked some kid
for his station wagon.

25:43.542 --> 25:45.152
Mark unit ran him down,

25:45.239 --> 25:46.806
but that just turned
into an ambush.

25:46.893 --> 25:49.939
at the switch car,
'bout, uh, six blocks over.

25:50.418 --> 25:54.857
All right. Get eyes out.
We're looking for something big.

25:54.944 --> 25:57.077
You know, something that
can carry all of them,

25:57.164 --> 25:58.687
something with power.

25:58.905 --> 26:00.994
We're talkin' a large SUV,
three-by-three, one ton.

26:01.081 --> 26:02.561
-Copy that.
-Yeah.

26:06.216 --> 26:07.914
Tell me about this van.

26:09.132 --> 26:11.700
Stole it. Three days,
out of Chalmette.

26:17.401 --> 26:19.099
-Nico
-Yes, sir.

26:20.666 --> 26:22.450
Who do we have over here?

26:22.537 --> 26:26.367
Bank tellers, managers
en route to University Medical.

26:26.454 --> 26:29.239
Heard he put up a fight,
and they tuned him up
pretty good.

26:29.326 --> 26:31.633
-Pssh... Not smart.
-No, sir.

26:34.767 --> 26:37.030
Hi. Now,
just one moment.

26:37.117 --> 26:40.381
Detective, do you mind
if I ask your witnesses
a couple questions?

26:40.468 --> 26:44.385
Seriously? I got a kid I was
supposed to pick up hours ago.

26:44.907 --> 26:48.171
-Go for it. I'm done.
-Thank you. Ladies...

26:48.258 --> 26:50.434
My name is Special Agent
Frank Ross.

26:50.521 --> 26:54.874
-Look... we just wanna go home.
-I understand. I do.

26:54.961 --> 26:57.833
I just need
a moment of your time.

26:58.399 --> 27:00.706
Do you remember anything...

27:00.793 --> 27:04.797
Anything specific about
the gunman who did this?

27:07.756 --> 27:10.803
-Two of 'em were Y'at.
-Y'at?

27:10.890 --> 27:12.631
I'm sorry, I'm sorry -I don't
know what a Y'at is--

27:12.718 --> 27:14.589
Metro locals. That Brooklyn
accent that you think

27:14.676 --> 27:16.460
you've been hearing around town?

27:16.547 --> 27:19.028
It ain't. That's a thing
we call Y'at.

27:19.115 --> 27:22.771
Okay. All right. Uh...
Which ones were Y'ats?

27:22.858 --> 27:24.860
The vampire and wolf.

27:24.947 --> 27:27.515
Okay. Thank you, thank you.
That's very, very helpful.

27:27.602 --> 27:28.690
Thank you very much.

27:28.777 --> 27:31.432
Ma'am, what about you?

27:31.519 --> 27:34.783
Did you see anything?
Do you remember anything?

27:35.915 --> 27:37.264
Ma'am?

27:38.004 --> 27:42.051
Guns. All I saw was guns.

27:44.053 --> 27:47.056
I mainly just kept my head down.
I didn't wanna...

27:47.143 --> 27:48.710
make eye contact.

27:49.929 --> 27:53.497
That was smart.
That was very smart.

27:54.150 --> 27:56.544
Okay, just breathe...
It's okay.

27:56.631 --> 27:58.677
-You're gonna be okay.
-[cell phone pings]

28:02.898 --> 28:04.770
Ex... excuse me, one moment.

28:11.341 --> 28:14.693
[girl] Dad, where are you?
I've been waiting forever.

28:14.780 --> 28:16.433
You're not coming, are you?

28:16.520 --> 28:19.175
Tomorrow morning
Works always first, right?

28:19.262 --> 28:21.482
-I should've known--
-Frank, I just got word...

28:21.569 --> 28:23.702
car fire on Chapitoulas.

28:36.062 --> 28:38.325
Ladies...
Thank you, thank you.

28:38.412 --> 28:41.720
Please don't hesitate to call
Detective here,

28:41.807 --> 28:44.635
if you remember
anything at all. Okay?

28:45.549 --> 28:48.422
All right?
Thank you all again.

28:49.597 --> 28:51.773
-Thanks, Agent Ross.
-Yeah.

28:54.428 --> 28:58.171
Get their details.
Run 'em all through local,
state, NCIC...

28:58.258 --> 29:00.216
-Will do.
-You drive.

29:01.261 --> 29:06.440
[suspenseful music]

29:14.796 --> 29:16.319
[pounding on door]

29:16.406 --> 29:18.713
-Who the f--
-Yo, Bill, open the door man.

29:18.800 --> 29:21.150
-Whoa whoa whoa whoa!
Bro...
-Yo, open the door, Bill.

29:21.237 --> 29:23.892
Whoa whoa whoa!
You can't bring him in here!

29:24.458 --> 29:26.416
Jeremy, this ain't how it works!

29:26.503 --> 29:27.896
[man gags]

29:28.027 --> 29:29.419
Tell me, motherfucker,
how's it work?

29:29.506 --> 29:31.247
How's it fucking work?

29:31.465 --> 29:33.380
-[man groans]
-Thought you'd rat us out,
didn't you?

29:33.467 --> 29:35.774
-Open your eyes,
I want you to see this.
-Hey, no no no.

29:35.861 --> 29:38.646
Come on,
he's as fucked as we are.
No no no, he fucking knew.

29:38.733 --> 29:40.909
He fucking knew.
You're the only one
who fuckin' knew.

29:40.996 --> 29:44.130
No, wrong. [coughs]
Smalls knew.

29:44.217 --> 29:46.785
-[coughs]
-What?

29:47.350 --> 29:50.571
When it hit the news,
I knew-- [coughs] I made a call.

29:52.181 --> 29:54.444
-NOPD picked him up
yesterday.

29:54.531 --> 29:57.012
-[coughs]
-Fuck.

29:57.665 --> 30:01.190
-We need another way out.
-Smalls didn't know
nothing about it.

30:01.277 --> 30:03.149
We don't know what the fuck he
knew, what he told him...

30:03.236 --> 30:06.587
-Hey, we need to wash
that shit ASAP.
-No can do.

30:06.674 --> 30:09.329
My guy's out.
Too much blood on it.

30:09.416 --> 30:11.722
-Blue blood.
-Oh, fuck that, fuck that.

30:11.810 --> 30:13.115
Tell him we'll give him
another bu--

30:13.202 --> 30:14.421
Tell him we'll give him
ten percent.

30:14.508 --> 30:15.857
[laughing] He's out!

30:16.031 --> 30:18.251
I don't care if you give him
100 percent!

30:18.338 --> 30:19.818
Jamie...

30:19.905 --> 30:21.558
It's too much heat.

30:21.645 --> 30:23.212
There's fucking
cash in a bag, right?

30:23.299 --> 30:25.562
Nobody's gonna fucking
clean that for us?

30:25.649 --> 30:27.303
[laughs] Yeah...

30:28.217 --> 30:31.742
The one guy I can dig up
that might be able to

30:31.830 --> 30:35.703
move that much weight...
[laughs]

30:35.921 --> 30:37.009
That's Nussy.

30:38.097 --> 30:41.840
And, boys,
the hit won't be light,

30:42.710 --> 30:47.541
Cause he's gonna take,
forty, fifty percent...
minimum.

30:49.412 --> 30:51.066
I mean, it is what it is, right?

30:52.459 --> 30:54.417
[Billy sighs]

30:55.288 --> 30:57.507
Fuck it. Make the fucking call.

30:57.594 --> 30:59.031
Yes, sir.

31:01.772 --> 31:04.079
Put your fucking guns down.
What the fuck!

31:04.166 --> 31:05.820
-Here we go-
Pearl, right?

31:05.907 --> 31:08.040
-What the fuck are you doin'?
-Fuck... you!

31:09.041 --> 31:10.869
You piece of shit.
You fucking coward.

31:10.956 --> 31:12.871
-Handle your business,
little bro--
-You fucking scum!

31:12.958 --> 31:14.524
I ain't got fucking time
for this--

31:14.742 --> 31:16.222
Fuck, you promised me, Jamie,
shit. You promised me--

31:16.309 --> 31:17.919
Get the fuck out of here.

31:18.006 --> 31:20.966
I'm gonna fucking kill you.
I'm gonna kill you.

31:21.053 --> 31:22.968
What are you doin'?!

31:23.577 --> 31:26.928
That psycho motherfucker
just killed us.

31:27.015 --> 31:28.843
Fuck! What was I thinking,
Jamie?

31:28.930 --> 31:30.889
We should've known better!
We should've known better.

31:30.976 --> 31:32.238
-[gasps] Fuck, Jamie!
-Hey.

31:32.325 --> 31:35.371
Joan! Joan!
The surgery was paid for.

31:35.458 --> 31:38.157
-Jamie, we had everything.
Jamie, everything is gone now.
-Shh... shh.

31:38.244 --> 31:41.203
-Stop.
-What... what?

31:41.377 --> 31:44.903
-What? [gasping]
-Come here.

31:51.431 --> 31:55.565
Listen. Hey... We're gonna
get through this, okay?

31:55.652 --> 31:57.698
All right?

31:58.612 --> 31:59.656
How?

31:59.743 --> 32:01.528
How? How do we get through this?

32:01.615 --> 32:02.833
I'm workin' on it.

32:03.008 --> 32:05.706
All right?
But you can't be here!

32:05.793 --> 32:08.404
We had a plan. You go home.

32:08.491 --> 32:10.232
You act like
everything is normal.

32:10.319 --> 32:13.540
You can't be around these guys,
all right?

32:15.368 --> 32:19.938
You need to listen to me.
The FBI's on you.

32:24.246 --> 32:25.552
They talk to you?

32:25.987 --> 32:29.077
Yeah, yeah. They were at
the bank for, like, hours.

32:29.164 --> 32:30.557
They talked to everybody.

32:30.644 --> 32:33.690
They're looking for guys
from the neighborhood.

32:36.041 --> 32:38.652
They're gonna find you, Jamie.
And... and...

32:38.739 --> 32:40.741
Listen... what if we just left.

32:41.220 --> 32:43.657
-What if we left right now...
and you came with me right now?
-Hey... Shh--

32:43.744 --> 32:45.267
-And we go get Joannie--
-Stop! Stop!

32:45.354 --> 32:47.226
And we get the fuck out of here.
You come with me...

32:47.313 --> 32:49.054
There's one thing
that's important. You go home.

32:49.141 --> 32:51.273
That's it.
Let me work!

32:51.665 --> 32:53.667
All right?
You trust me?

32:53.754 --> 32:55.060
-[man screaming]
-You know I do.

32:56.931 --> 32:59.107
I can't have this.
You gotta get him out of here.

32:59.194 --> 33:00.717
Shut the door! Shut the door!

33:00.804 --> 33:02.284
Jamie, he's gotta go!

33:02.371 --> 33:03.764
Where the fuck
am I gonna take him, Bill?

33:03.851 --> 33:06.201
-Let's take him to Clarence.
-[coughing]

33:06.288 --> 33:08.073
We ain't takin' him
to fucking Clarence's.

33:08.160 --> 33:10.118
Dump him at the E.R.
and hope for the best.

33:10.205 --> 33:12.425
-Take him to--
-Take him to fucking Clarence.

33:12.512 --> 33:13.774
I'm coming with.

33:13.861 --> 33:15.471
-What?
-Yeah.

33:15.732 --> 33:17.952
No you're fucking going home.
We just talked about this.

33:18.039 --> 33:21.129
I ain't leavin' you here
with this fucking psychopath.

33:23.044 --> 33:26.178
-Ava.
-No way! I'm not going home!

33:27.875 --> 33:29.877
You know what?
That's a great idea.

33:29.964 --> 33:32.271
Cops ain't looking
for no pretty brunette
from the Channel.

33:32.358 --> 33:34.229
Here! You drive!

33:41.671 --> 33:44.370
I'm not leaving your side
till this is over with.

33:45.806 --> 33:49.505
You fuck us...and I will be back
to murder you where you stand.

33:49.592 --> 33:50.898
We clear?

33:51.029 --> 33:54.032
-[suspenseful music]
-We're clear.

33:57.861 --> 33:59.211
[reporter]
The surviving assailants

33:59.298 --> 34:00.777
are believed to have made off

34:00.908 --> 34:03.128
with over one point five
million dollars.

34:03.215 --> 34:05.086
The New Orleans Police
Department,

34:05.304 --> 34:08.306
in conjunction with the FBI's
elite robbery task force unit

34:08.393 --> 34:10.351
have begun
an extensive manhunt.

34:10.438 --> 34:12.920
Setting up roadblocks
and checkpoints.

34:13.007 --> 34:15.444
Effectively shutting down
all access points

34:15.531 --> 34:17.489
both in and out of the city.

34:17.577 --> 34:19.882
If you, or anyone you know,

34:19.969 --> 34:21.885
has any information on
the whereabouts

34:21.972 --> 34:23.670
of these fugitives,

34:23.757 --> 34:25.802
the New Orleans Police
Department asks that

34:25.889 --> 34:27.543
you contact them immediately.

34:27.630 --> 34:29.154
But do not approach.

34:29.763 --> 34:32.853
The assailants are considered
armed and extremely dangerous.

34:34.246 --> 34:37.466
Now, let's go to George,
who's standing by
at University Medical,

34:37.553 --> 34:39.512
-awaiting an update
on the state,
-[phone buzzes]

34:39.599 --> 34:42.254
of the officers wounded
in today's heinous attack.

34:42.341 --> 34:45.170
-Yo
-[George over TV] Hank,
the situation at the hospital

34:45.257 --> 34:48.303
-Who's this?
- at the hospital
is extremely grim.

34:48.389 --> 34:50.391
-Oh, yeah.
- And with good reason.

34:50.478 --> 34:51.958
-Today's tragic events--
-Yo, Nussy.

34:52.045 --> 34:53.612
marked the deadliest incident--

34:53.699 --> 34:55.918
Got some fool on the line
that says you knows him.

34:56.659 --> 34:58.748
Told me to tell ya,
he's willing to chat.

35:00.228 --> 35:04.232
[television broadcast continues]

35:06.800 --> 35:09.542
The Jet,
what you want?

35:09.629 --> 35:12.414
[broadcaster] Some
arriving, still unaware.
of whether their loved ones

35:12.501 --> 35:14.068
Yeah, I'm lookin' at that shit
right now.

35:14.503 --> 35:17.115
These some straight up
mad motherfuckers,
right here.

35:18.855 --> 35:21.815
-Oh, yeah? Enlighten me.
-[news continues in background]

35:23.904 --> 35:28.343
[suspenseful music plays]

35:41.791 --> 35:43.967
It's a good location
to dump a car.

35:44.054 --> 35:46.100
You got 90 only seconds away,

35:46.187 --> 35:48.537
and the Irish Channel
to get lost in, right there.

35:49.843 --> 35:51.584
So, what's next?

35:52.933 --> 35:55.718
We flex this. Okay?

35:55.805 --> 35:56.893
So what do we know?

35:56.980 --> 35:58.678
Three shooters. One's hurtin'.

35:58.765 --> 36:00.723
Two of 'em are
probably local boys.

36:00.810 --> 36:02.377
All ex-military.

36:02.551 --> 36:05.685
Not just military...
these guys are gunfighters.

36:05.772 --> 36:08.862
We're lookin' for vets
with trigger time
in the sandbox.

36:08.949 --> 36:10.646
I'll get Jean
to reach out to DOD.

36:10.733 --> 36:13.171
-And I'll pull Jefferson
and Orleans' barrage.
-Good.

36:14.694 --> 36:16.478
So what exactly was the take?

36:16.565 --> 36:19.220
Walked out with three mil,
got away with one point five.

36:20.917 --> 36:23.659
What was a bank in East Calhoun
doing with that much cash?

36:23.746 --> 36:25.487
They just took over
the temp headquarters branch,

36:25.574 --> 36:28.186
because the CBD location
was going through a remodel.

36:29.491 --> 36:30.840
And today's Thursday.

36:31.711 --> 36:34.496
So, they were carrying
heavy prepping' for distribution

36:34.583 --> 36:35.976
to all the other branches.

36:36.063 --> 36:38.065
Cover all those
Friday payroll checks.

36:38.413 --> 36:39.980
And, how do they know all this?

36:40.067 --> 36:41.677
That's our job.

36:43.679 --> 36:46.204
You mentioned earlier,
an Edwin Smalls...

36:46.291 --> 36:48.380
That's right. The rat.

36:48.467 --> 36:50.643
Smalls gave them intel
and boards.

36:50.730 --> 36:52.035
What kind of boards?

36:52.122 --> 36:53.515
Some high-end, custom stuff,

36:53.602 --> 36:55.648
designed to trigger
the alarm system

36:55.865 --> 36:58.520
-to shut itself off 15 minutes
before the crew hit the place.
-Okay.

36:58.607 --> 37:01.306
I followed up on that
with the bank's security firm.

37:01.393 --> 37:04.352
They told me that they found
two odd, custom boards

37:04.439 --> 37:06.485
installed in the master CPU.

37:06.572 --> 37:09.531
They're polygraphing
the entire staff as we speak.

37:11.229 --> 37:13.840
So if Smalls hadn't talked,
they'd have gotten away clean?

37:13.927 --> 37:15.276
Hundred percent.

37:16.364 --> 37:17.626
Hmm...

37:18.236 --> 37:20.281
I wanna speak to this nobody.

37:20.368 --> 37:22.675
This Mr. Edwin Smalls.

37:29.508 --> 37:34.339
[suspenseful music]

37:42.869 --> 37:44.523
[knocks on door]

37:48.048 --> 37:51.312
Holy shit.
Get the fuck out of here.

37:51.834 --> 37:54.010
-We need you.
-[grunts]

37:54.097 --> 37:55.708
I got you. Come on!

37:55.795 --> 37:58.145
Get the hell in here! Quick!
Put him over here.

38:00.452 --> 38:02.367
Put him over here.
Put him over here.

38:02.454 --> 38:03.672
Sorry 'bout the mess, man.

38:03.846 --> 38:05.108
I was about to
clean this shit up.

38:05.195 --> 38:06.849
-[coughing]
-Put him right here.

38:08.024 --> 38:11.941
[breathes heavily]

38:15.902 --> 38:19.166
-Bullet hit him
under his armpit.
-[coughs]

38:19.253 --> 38:23.083
-His right armpit.
-His other right armpit,
Clarence!

38:23.170 --> 38:25.694
-Where the fucking blood is!
-Would you just chill out, man?!

38:25.781 --> 38:27.957
You got me so fucking rattled,
I can't even think straight!

38:28.044 --> 38:30.438
I got this.
Just let me do my thing!

38:30.525 --> 38:32.614
[woman]
Clarence! Who's that?

38:32.701 --> 38:35.356
-Who the fuck is that?
-[woman] Who you got in there?

38:36.531 --> 38:39.882
Ma! It's the pie guy.
He's just droppin' off a
pepperoni.

38:39.969 --> 38:41.667
[woman]
But I hate pepperoni!

38:41.754 --> 38:44.800
Yeah, I know!
It's not for you! It's for me.

38:44.887 --> 38:47.281
-You said you didn't want any.
-[man grunts]

38:47.368 --> 38:51.111
-That ain't no pie guy!
-Mom, just relax, okay?

38:51.198 --> 38:53.156
I'll be there in a bit
to rub your feet.

38:53.243 --> 38:55.681
-[woman] Really?
-I promise, Ma!

38:55.768 --> 38:59.467
Just watch your program,
and I'll be in there
before it's over.

38:59.685 --> 39:02.383
[grunts]

39:04.080 --> 39:07.736
-Yo, what the fuck
are you doin'?
-I--I--I need my bag.

39:07.823 --> 39:10.348
-What bag?
-It's a medical bag.

39:10.435 --> 39:11.958
It's green. It's about this big.

39:19.139 --> 39:21.620
-This it?
-That's it. Toss it here.

39:21.707 --> 39:24.013
Now, everybody
just give me my space,

39:24.100 --> 39:25.580
and let me do my thing.

39:26.581 --> 39:28.453
[cell phone vibrates]

39:32.587 --> 39:34.328
-It's Bill.
-Take it. I got it.

39:34.415 --> 39:36.809
-You got this?
-Yeah, I got it. Go go go go go.

39:36.896 --> 39:38.985
Hey, what's up?

39:40.595 --> 39:41.988
What you got?

39:42.684 --> 39:46.949
He's down, but it's a shit deal.

39:47.602 --> 39:49.038
Thirty cents on the dollar.

39:49.125 --> 39:50.910
Fuck, that's seventy percent.

39:50.997 --> 39:56.437
I know, but it's one of those
take-it-or-leave-it situations.

39:58.526 --> 40:00.136
Your call.

40:00.223 --> 40:04.532
[suspenseful music plays]

40:05.751 --> 40:08.841
-All right.
-How's the bleeding?

40:08.928 --> 40:11.974
Not good.
So how we gonna do this?

40:15.238 --> 40:18.720
This dude has lost
a shit ton of blood.

40:19.808 --> 40:21.201
My guess is the bullet
bounced off his shoulders,

40:21.288 --> 40:22.898
start gettin' down
to his stomach.

40:24.030 --> 40:26.249
His abdomen is distended,
and he's got a G.I. bleed.

40:26.336 --> 40:27.729
I ain't got time for this, Bro.

40:27.816 --> 40:29.514
Well, I don't know
what to tell you, bro!

40:29.601 --> 40:31.516
