and put another
in critical condition.

52:59.611 --> 53:02.788
Which makes you an accessory to,
at minimum...

53:02.875 --> 53:05.312
Six counts of capital murder.

53:08.533 --> 53:11.840
Now, you're realizing
the gravity of your situation.

53:11.927 --> 53:16.062
All right, look. I had no
fucking idea, all right?

53:16.149 --> 53:17.933
They were supposed to go in
on the prowl.

53:18.020 --> 53:19.631
Break in the night before.

53:19.718 --> 53:21.328
Look, I had no idea
they were gonna kill no one,

53:21.415 --> 53:23.722
-all right?
-I'm sure the state of Louisiana

53:23.809 --> 53:26.072
would really appreciate
that explanation.

53:29.554 --> 53:31.295
Oh, fuck me.

53:31.382 --> 53:33.862
Yeah, yeah, that's about right.

53:36.561 --> 53:38.476
All right, look, look...

53:38.563 --> 53:39.868
What can I do, all right?

53:39.955 --> 53:41.522
Tell me, tell me...
What can I do?

53:41.609 --> 53:43.655
Tell me 'bout your customers.

53:43.742 --> 53:46.266
These guys that put you
in this hole.

53:46.353 --> 53:50.139
Okay, it was, uh,
two White dudes.

53:50.227 --> 53:51.706
I think they might've
been brothers.

53:51.793 --> 53:53.273
How'd you come
to that conclusion?

53:53.969 --> 53:55.754
They kept calling each other
bro and shit.

53:55.884 --> 53:57.103
What are you, fucking Redman?
Who do you know in this city

53:57.190 --> 53:58.452
who doesn't call each other bro?

53:58.670 --> 54:00.237
It was different than that,
all right?

54:00.541 --> 54:01.934
Look I just-- I feel like
they were brothers. All right?

54:02.021 --> 54:04.066
-They kind of looked alike.
-Okay, okay.

54:04.153 --> 54:07.548
This is good. Tell me more
about these brothers.

54:07.635 --> 54:12.118
All right, uh, they, uh...
The younger one
was the smart one.

54:12.771 --> 54:16.818
Okay? And--and...
The older one was the mean one.

54:16.905 --> 54:18.864
